import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    for i, series in enumerate(data['Series'].unique()):
        subset = data[data['Series'] == series]
        plt.scatter(subset['X'], subset['Y'], label=series)
    
    plt.xlabel('X')
    plt.ylabel('Y')
    plt.legend(title='Series')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What is the correlation between X and Y for each set in Anscombe's Quartet?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data_series = data.groupby('Series')
    
    x_data = []
    y_data = []
    labels = []
    
    for name, group in data_series:
        x_data.append(group['X'])
        y_data.append(group['Y'])
        labels.append(name)
    
    plt.boxplot(x_data, positions=[i*2 for i in range(len(labels))], widths=0.6)
    plt.boxplot(y_data, positions=[i*2+1 for i in range(len(labels))], widths=0.6)
    
    plt.xticks(range(0, len(labels)*2, 2), labels)
    plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What is the mean and standard deviation of X and Y for each set in Anscombe's Quartet?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    for i, series in enumerate(data['Series'].unique()):
        plt.subplot(2, 2, i + 1)
        series_data = data[data['Series'] == series]
        plt.hist(series_data['X'], alpha=0.5, label='X')
        plt.hist(series_data['Y'], alpha=0.5, label='Y')
        plt.title(f'Series {series}')
        plt.legend()
        if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
            plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.suptitle("What is the distribution of X and Y for each set in Anscombe's Quartet?", wrap=True)
    plt.tight_layout(rect=[0, 0.03, 1, 0.95])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
